            . I am a <rs id="t18170917-24-viclabel124" type="occupation">boot-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-24-victim210 t18170917-24-viclabel124"></join>, and live in Cow-lane, Smithfield. On the 27th of August, about half-past ten o'clock at night, my boot was in my shop-window; I was coming from the other side of the street, and saw the prisoner in the shop, I stopped to watch him, saw him take up a boot, and come towards the door with it; I caught hold of him as he came out, took it from him, and gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I picked it up.</p>
